# Git Policy

- **NEVER** run `git commit`, `git push`, `git merge`, `git rebase`, or any command that modifies git history.
- You MAY run `git add` to stage files.
- You MAY run read-only git commands: `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, `git branch`, `git show`.
- When the user asks to commit, stage the relevant files with `git add` and provide a suggested commit message — do not execute the commit.
